  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Physical activity is a well-known and powerful tool in medicine,having preventive,&#xD;
      palliative, and curative properties. This has not been sufficiently examined in children in&#xD;
      remission from cancer. In this study, children in remission from cancer will be divided into&#xD;
      exercise and control groups. The interventional group will perform two supervised, 60-minute&#xD;
      weekly exercise sessions. Outcome measures of the exercise intervention will be quality of&#xD;
      life, mood, cardiorespiratory fitness, body composition and bone mineral density.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
